mdmNetworkConfigTable.name: mdmNetworkConfigTable
mdmNetworkConfigTable.description: The GDC VFAST modem network configuration table.

mdmNetworkEntry.name: mdmNetworkEntry
mdmNetworkEntry.description: A listing of GDC VFAST modem network options.

mdmNetworkIndex.name: mdmNetworkIndex
mdmNetworkIndex.description: A unique index for the Network Table.

mdmNetworkType.name: mdmNetworkType
mdmNetworkType.description: Command to option the VF line type mode of operation.

mdmSNTxType.name: mdmSNTxType
mdmSNTxType.description: Command used to select either Permissive or Programable Switched Network Transmit Level. This object is Country Code dependent

mdmSNTxLevel.name: mdmSNTxLevel
mdmSNTxLevel.description: Command to select(force) the Switched Network Transmit Level when modem is optioned for adjustable. This object is Country Code dependent

mdmSNHandshakeMode.name: mdmSNHandshakeMode
mdmSNHandshakeMode.description: Available handshake modes. This object is Country Code dependent.

mdmDTEConfigTable.name: mdmDTEConfigTable
mdmDTEConfigTable.description: The GDC VFAST modem Data Terminal Equipment configuration table.

mdmDTEntry.name: mdmDTEntry
mdmDTEntry.description: A listing of GDC VFAST modem DTE options.

mdmDTEIndex.name: mdmDTEIndex
mdmDTEIndex.description: A unique index for the DTE Table.

mdmDTESpeed.name: mdmDTESpeed
mdmDTESpeed.description: This option selects DTE bit Rate.

mdmCPMResp.name: mdmCPMResp
mdmCPMResp.description: Selects the response rate of the Call Progress Monitor.

mdmCharLength.name: mdmCharLength
mdmCharLength.description: DTE charater length and format options of the DTE asynchronous data.

mdmParity.name: mdmParity
mdmParity.description: Parity of the async data when the character length option selects parity.

mdmOverspeed.name: mdmOverspeed
mdmOverspeed.description: Option to set DTE async overspeed data tolerated by the modem. Extended = 2.5%. Nominal = 1.25%.

mdmFlowCntrl.name: mdmFlowCntrl
mdmFlowCntrl.description: Options to set the modem DTE flow control. disable Disables all flow control. xonXoffSig Enables XON/XOFF signaling between modem and DTE. cts Enables the modem to flow control the DTE via CTS. rtsCts This option operates the same as CTS option as well as allowing RTS to flow control the modem as a ready to receive signal. xonOff Allows the modem to XON/XOFF the DTE yet ignore these signals when sent by the DTE (unidirectional flow control).

mdmTermEcho.name: mdmTermEcho
mdmTermEcho.description: Option to control the modem echo to the DTE.

mdmDCDCntrl.name: mdmDCDCntrl
mdmDCDCntrl.description: Option the EIA DCD mode of operation. ForceOn DCD always ON. Real DCD will follow CCITT specifications. ForceOnToggleDisc DCD is On but toggle on disconnect as a signaling to the front end.

mdmCTSCntrl.name: mdmCTSCntrl
mdmCTSCntrl.description: Option the EIA CTS mode of operation. cmdOnDataRTS On during command mode, during data mode will follow RTS. cmdOnDataReal On during command mode, during data mode will follow CCITT specifications. realCCITT It follows CCITT specifications always. ForceON On all the times.

mdmDTRTrans.name: mdmDTRTrans
mdmDTRTrans.description: Option the modem to respond to loss of DTR. forceon Modem ignore DTR transitions. offInCmdMode Upon transition detection modem will enter command mode. offDisc Upon transition detection modem will disconnect. offDiscRecalUser Upon transition detection modem will disconect and recall the selected User configuration. This object is Country Code dependent.

mdmDSRCntrl.name: mdmDSRCntrl
mdmDSRCntrl.description: Option the EIA DSR mode of operation. onUntilDisc Selects DSR to remain On and glitch Off for disconnect. Normal Causes DSR to be real. followDCD Selects DSR to follow carrier detect. forceOn Selects DSR forced On in all modes.

mdmDSRCntrlAL.name: mdmDSRCntrlAL
mdmDSRCntrlAL.description: Option the EIA DSR operation during analoop. onAnaloop DSR will turn ON when in analoop offAnaloop DSR is forced Off when in Analoop.

mdmTXClockSource.name: mdmTXClockSource
mdmTXClockSource.description: Selects the source for TX clock generation. internal The modem uses the internally generated clock source. external The modem uses the DTE clock as a source receiverwrap The modem receiver derived timing clock to be used in the transmitter.

mdmRTSCTSDelay.name: mdmRTSCTSDelay
mdmRTSCTSDelay.description: Selects the delay time between RTS coming on and CTS being turned on (.001 sec).

mdmCarriageReturnCharacter.name: mdmCarriageReturnCharacter
mdmCarriageReturnCharacter.description: Select the ascii character to be used as the carriage return.

mdmCharacterAbortDialing.name: mdmCharacterAbortDialing
mdmCharacterAbortDialing.description: Enable/disable the option to abort dialing if a DTE character is detected.

mdmDelayDTR.name: mdmDelayDTR
mdmDelayDTR.description: Selects the delay time(in Seconds) between making data mode and raising the DTR lead. It is dependent on the mode of operation. When configured for &M0 this register is used to debounce the DTR signal. The default value is five hundredths of a second (0.05second). When configured for &M1 and in data mode, this register sets the time available to the operator to switch the EIA cable from asynchronous equipment to synchronous equipment. When the timer expires, this register is used to debounce the DTR signal as in &M0 mode. The default value is five seconds.

mdmEscapeCharacter.name: mdmEscapeCharacter
mdmEscapeCharacter.description: Select the ascii character to be used as the 'escape to command mode' character.

mdmLineFeedCharacter.name: mdmLineFeedCharacter
mdmLineFeedCharacter.description: Select the ascii character to be used as the Line Feed character.

mdmHangUpDelay.name: mdmHangUpDelay
mdmHangUpDelay.description: Select the delay time(in Sec) between the modem detecting a command to hang up the line and the disconnect operation.

mdmEscapeCharacterGuardTime.name: mdmEscapeCharacterGuardTime
mdmEscapeCharacterGuardTime.description: This is the timer the modem will use when determining a valid escape sequence. Select the delay time(in 1/50 Sec). When a valid escape sequence is detected the modem will transfer from the data to command mode.

mdmOperatingMode.name: mdmOperatingMode
mdmOperatingMode.description: Option to set the type of data transfer in data mode. asyncDataMode modem operates in async mode during command or data mode. async CmdsyncData In command mode the modem uses async data. In data mode operates in synchronous mode.

mdmBackSpaceCharacter.name: mdmBackSpaceCharacter
mdmBackSpaceCharacter.description: Select the ascii character to be used as the Back Space character.

mdmModemConfigTable.name: mdmModemConfigTable
mdmModemConfigTable.description: The GDC VFAST modem configuration table.

mdmModemEntry.name: mdmModemEntry
mdmModemEntry.description: A listing of GDC VFAST modem options.

mdmModemIndex.name: mdmModemIndex
mdmModemIndex.description: A unique index for the Modem Option Table.

mdmRingsToAns.name: mdmRingsToAns
mdmRingsToAns.description: Selects the number of rings received before the modem Auto Answer. This object is Country Code dependent

mdmFallFwrdBack.name: mdmFallFwrdBack
mdmFallFwrdBack.description: Command the modem to enable/disable rate negotiation during a retrain.

mdmTrellis.name: mdmTrellis
mdmTrellis.description: Enable/disable Trellis negotiation during a handshake.

mdmSQRetrain.name: mdmSQRetrain
mdmSQRetrain.description: Command to option Signal Quality Retrains.

mdmLongSpaceDisc.name: mdmLongSpaceDisc
mdmLongSpaceDisc.description: Command to enable/disable Long Space Disconnect. enable The modem will transmit 4 seconds of continuous space (BREAK) when ever a disconnect request is detected. If the modem receives more than 1.5 seconds of continuous space (BREAK) while on-line, it will hang up.

mdmMakeBusy.name: mdmMakeBusy
mdmMakeBusy.description: Command to option the switched network make busy function disable Does not make busy. onLossDTR Make busy on loss of DTR. inAL Make busy during analoop. inALorLossRTSorDTR Make busy in analoop, loss of RTS or DTR. This object is Country Code dependent

mdmRDLOptions.name: mdmRDLOptions
mdmRDLOptions.description: Command to enable/disable Remote Digital Loopback Instigation. disable The modem ignores the inband request to initiate a remote digital loopback. enable The modem accept the inband request to initiated a remote digital loopback.

mdmTestTimer.name: mdmTestTimer
mdmTestTimer.description: Command to limit any diagnostic test in 10 second intervals. When the value is zero the test runs forever.

mdmDTETestCntrl.name: mdmDTETestCntrl
mdmDTETestCntrl.description: Command to enable/disable diagnostic tests from DTE interface.

mdmDCDLossDisc.name: mdmDCDLossDisc
mdmDCDLossDisc.description: Command to set the time (0.1sec) between loss of carrier detected and a modem disconnect. This object is Country Code dependent.

mdmCDRespTime.name: mdmCDRespTime
mdmCDRespTime.description: Command to set the time (in Sec) a carrier signal must be present for the modem to recognize it. This object is Country Code dependent.

mdmAnswerOriginate.name: mdmAnswerOriginate
mdmAnswerOriginate.description: Command to set the handshake band. answerIfRingDetect Upon detecting a ring the modem will handshake in the answer mode. forceAnswer The modem will be force to handshake in the answer mode. autoAnswerInOriginate When the modem detect a ring it will answer in the originate mode.

mdmWaitForDCD.name: mdmWaitForDCD
mdmWaitForDCD.description: This object is used to store the carrier wait time. This is the time which the modem will wait after the dial has been completed until the modem senses carrier detect. It is also used for the dial command modifiers W wait for dial tone before dialing and @ wait for quiet answer before dialing. It also sets the amount of time the modem will wait for ringback when originating a call. This object is Country Code dependent.

mdmDialerConfigTable.name: mdmDialerConfigTable
mdmDialerConfigTable.description: The GDC VFAST dialer configuration table.

mdmDialerEntry.name: mdmDialerEntry
mdmDialerEntry.description: A listing of GDC VFAST modem dialer options.

mdmDialerIndex.name: mdmDialerIndex
mdmDialerIndex.description: A unique index for the Dialer Table.

mdmCPMMonitor.name: mdmCPMMonitor
mdmCPMMonitor.description: Command used to option the Call Progress Monitor operation. This object is Country Code dependent. basic The modem will blind dial and will only send a CONNECT message for all established links. All CPM is disabled. extendedNoCPM This command is the same as basic with the exception of the connect messages. The modem will send the appropiate connect response of CONNECT followed by the connected speed. extendedDialTone This command is the same as extendedNoCPM command but without blind dialing. The modem will send the NO DIALTONE message if dial tone is not detected. extendedBusy This command forces the modem to blind dial. The modem will not respond with the NO DIALTONE message while all other CPM responses are enabled. extendedFullCPM This command enables all CPM response codes and monitoring, except rinback detection. extendedFullCPMRingback This command enables all CPM response codes and monitoring, and includes ringback detection. This object is Country Code dependent.

mdmParserSelection.name: mdmParserSelection
mdmParserSelection.description: Command used to select the DTE parser. The following parsers are available: AT, v25async, v25HDLC, v25bisync, and no parser

mdmDTRDial.name: mdmDTRDial
mdmDTRDial.description: This command sets the modem operation upon detecting an Off to On transition on DTR. disable Transition is ignored. cellNumber0 Dial number stored in cell 0. cellNumber1 Dial number stored in cell 1. cellNumber2 Dial number stored in cell 2. cellNumber3 Dial number stored in cell 3. cellNumber4 Dial number stored in cell 4. cellNumber5 Dial number stored in cell 5. cellNumber6 Dial number stored in cell 6. cellNumber7 Dial number stored in cell 7. cellNumber8 Dial number stored in cell 8. cellNumber9 Dial number stored in cell 9. talkData Starts a handshake.

mdmDialType.name: mdmDialType
mdmDialType.description: This command selects the type of dial. Pulse or DTMF dial. This object is Country Code dependent

mdmResponseMode.name: mdmResponseMode
mdmResponseMode.description: This Command controls when to send responses. enabled Requests the non-quiet mode, that is, to transmit result codes to the DTE as appropriate. disabled Request the quiet mode which tells the modem not to send any result codes to the DTE. enableInOriginate Disables Call Progress Monitor responses in the answer mode only. This mode is entered on detection of ring signal.

mdmResponseType.name: mdmResponseType
mdmResponseType.description: This command controls the type of responses. numeric modem responses are in numeric code. alpha modem responses are in alphabetical format.

mdmPauseTime.name: mdmPauseTime
mdmPauseTime.description: This command selects the time for pause characters in the dial string. This object is Country Code dependent.

mdmWaitForDialtoneTime.name: mdmWaitForDialtoneTime
mdmWaitForDialtoneTime.description: This command selects the time for the modem to be looking for dialtone before disconnecting. This object is Country Code dependent

mdmProtocolConfigTable.name: mdmProtocolConfigTable
mdmProtocolConfigTable.description: The GDC VFAST modem Protocol configuration table.

mdmProtocolEntry.name: mdmProtocolEntry
mdmProtocolEntry.description: A listing of GDC VFAST modem Protocol options.

mdmProtocolIndex.name: mdmProtocolIndex
mdmProtocolIndex.description: A unique index for the DTE Table.

mdmCompression.name: mdmCompression
mdmCompression.description: This command controls the Compression operation when operating in asynchronous mode. disabled No compression available. enabled Compression available in both directions. txpathonly Compression available in the transmitter path only when in V.42bis. In MNP 5 data compression is enabled in both directions. rxpathonly Compression available in the receiver path only when in V.42bis. In MNP 5 data compression is enabled in both directions.

mdmAsyncProtocol.name: mdmAsyncProtocol
mdmAsyncProtocol.description: This command controls the Protocols available at the handshake. wire Options the modem to run in wire mode; copying characters from VF port to the DTE port and vice versa. direct Options the modem to run in direct mode; where the DTE and the VF speeds must match, and there is no speed buffering. Direct mode is V.14 asynchronous mode. mnpreliable This option limits error correction to MNP links only or hang up. autoreliable Options the mode to run in autoreliable mode, and the modem will negotiate V.42 or alternate links. With no link, the modem will enter wire mode (speed buffering). v42reliable This option limits error correction to a V.42 (LAPM) link or hang up. reliableLAPMorMNP This option will attempt either a V.42 (LAPM) or MNP link and if either link fails, the modem will hang up. V.13 This option selects V.13 simulated controlled carrier.

mdmFlowControl.name: mdmFlowControl
mdmFlowControl.description: This command controls the flow control type between the modem and the DTE available at the handshake. disabled Disables modem to modem flow control. enabled Enables bidirectional modem flow control based on XON/XOFF signaling. These signals are detected, acted on and optionally deleted from the data stream. Unidirectional provides unidirectional flow control where a modem may send XON/XOFF signals to the remote modem, yet ignore and pass through any these VF received signals to its DTE. bidirectional Acts the same as enabled with the addition of the XON/XOFF pass through option being enabled.

mdmBreakHandling.name: mdmBreakHandling
mdmBreakHandling.description: This command controls the operation of breaks. expediteDest This option will immediately transmit a break character for a fix time (300 msec) and destroy any currently bufered data. expediteNonDest This option is the same as expediteDest except all buffered data will be save. nonExpediteNonDest This option will transmit a fixed time break character in sequence with the rest of the data. ignore Ignores all break received from the DTE. timedNonExoediteNonDest This option transmits break characters in sequence with the rest of the data for the duration the DTE is transmitting this character. timedNonExpediteNonDest2 Same as above.

mdmConnAndLinkMessages.name: mdmConnAndLinkMessages
mdmConnAndLinkMessages.description: This command controls when to send the protocol messages. separateMessages This options the modem to send the standard GDC conect message upon reaching data mode plus V.42 message after the link negotiation. The connect message displays VF line speed. bothAfterLink With this option the connect and link messages are send after link negotiation. microcomCompatible This option is the same as bothAfterLink except adds a /RELIABLE at the end of the message when a V.42 error corrected link has been establish. connectAfterLink This option sends only the connect message after the link negotiation. The message will indicate the VF rate for V.13 and V.14 connections and the DTE rate for all other connections.

mdmErrorCorrection.name: mdmErrorCorrection
mdmErrorCorrection.description: This command controls how the data is handled when running a protocol. noBuffer This option discards all data coming in from the modem until the receiver modem sends a PROTOCOL: NONE message to the DTE at which time data will be passed through. bufferRxData This option will buffer received data (up to 200 characters) until the PROTOCOL: NONE message is sent. The buffered data will be passed through to the DTE. The modem will fall back to wire mode if more than 200 characters have been received prior to establishing an error correction link. fallbackWithFallbackChar This command discards all incoming data until two consecutive fallback characters are detected at which point the receiver modem falls back to wire mode. One fallback character is passed through to its DTE as data. fallbackV14Buffer This option acts the same as bufferRxData except with no link it falls back to V.14 (direct)mode. fallbackV14WithFallbackChar This option acts as fallbackWithFallbackChar except it also falls back to V.14 (direct) mode.

mdmV13Mode.name: mdmV13Mode
mdmV13Mode.description: This command controls the V13 function. bidirectional Selects bidirectional V.13 simulated controlled carrier. txEnable Selects V.13 Tx side enabled. rxEnable Selects V.13 RX side enabled.

mdmSyncProtocol.name: mdmSyncProtocol
mdmSyncProtocol.description: This command controls the type of sync protocol. normalsync Selects normal synchronous mode. v13sync Selects synchronous V13 mode.

mdmFrameRetransLimit.name: mdmFrameRetransLimit
mdmFrameRetransLimit.description: This command limits the number of times the modem will retransmit a frame while in an error correction connection.

mdmPrivateLineConfigTable.name: mdmPrivateLineConfigTable
mdmPrivateLineConfigTable.description: The GDC VFAST modem Private Line configuration table.

mdmPrivateLineEntry.name: mdmPrivateLineEntry
mdmPrivateLineEntry.description: A listing of GDC VFAST Private Line configurations options.

mdmPrivateLineIndex.name: mdmPrivateLineIndex
mdmPrivateLineIndex.description: A unique index for the Private Line Configurations Table.

mdmPrivateLineTxLevel.name: mdmPrivateLineTxLevel
mdmPrivateLineTxLevel.description: This command selects the transmit level during Private Line operation. This object is Country Code dependent

mdmPrivateLineHandshakeMode.name: mdmPrivateLineHandshakeMode
mdmPrivateLineHandshakeMode.description: This command selects the Private Line Handshake modes

mdmAutoDialRestoral.name: mdmAutoDialRestoral
mdmAutoDialRestoral.description: This command selects the options for Auto Dial Restoral when the modem is in private line mode. disabled No Auto Dial Restoral allowed. enableWithEndOfSession Enable Auto Dial Restoral with line failure indicator. enableWithoutEnOfSession Enable Auto Dial Restoral without line failure indicator.

mdmPrivateLineDownTime.name: mdmPrivateLineDownTime
mdmPrivateLineDownTime.description: This command selects for how long the Private Line must be lost before going to Dial Back Up mode

mdmDBUtoPLLookbackTime.name: mdmDBUtoPLLookbackTime
mdmDBUtoPLLookbackTime.description: This command selects the time for how often the modem must lookback for Private Line restoral. The units are in 10 minutes. Valid range from 0 to 255. When the value 0 is selected this option is disabled.

mdmAlarmScanTable.name: mdmAlarmScanTable
mdmAlarmScanTable.description: The GDC VFAST alarm Scan Table.

mdmAlarmScanEntry.name: mdmAlarmScanEntry
mdmAlarmScanEntry.description: An entry in the GDC VFAST alarm table.

mdmAlarmScanIndex.name: mdmAlarmScanIndex
mdmAlarmScanIndex.description: This object is the identifier of the VFAST alarm table.

mdmAlarmScan.name: mdmAlarmScan
mdmAlarmScan.description: Reads the alarm scan. There are 8 bytes. byte 1 bit 4 (bit 1.4) No DTR signal bit 2.0 No TXD Transitions bit 2.2 No RXD Transitions bit 2.3 Modem Fallback bit 2.6 Modem on Dial Back Up bit 3.2 Power Up bit 4.0 Poor Signal Quality bit 5.3 DCD Loss bit 6.0-6 no alarms bit 7.0 Modem Configuration Checksum Error bit 7.1 Call Failed bit 7.2 Call Length Exceeded Maximum Allowed bit 7.3 Retrain Count Exceeded Threshold bit 7.4 Ring No Answer bit 7.5 Remote Configuration session active bit 7.6 Test timeout bit 8.0-6 no alarms

mdmResetSelfPowerBit.name: mdmResetSelfPowerBit
mdmResetSelfPowerBit.description: This resets the modem power up alarm.

mdmMaskAlarmTable.name: mdmMaskAlarmTable
mdmMaskAlarmTable.description: The GDC VFAST alarm Mask Table.

mdmMaskAlarmEntry.name: mdmMaskAlarmEntry
mdmMaskAlarmEntry.description: An entry in the GDC VFAST alarm mask table.

mdmMaskAlarmIndex.name: mdmMaskAlarmIndex
mdmMaskAlarmIndex.description: This object is the index of the VFAST alarm mask table.

mdmDTRLoss.name: mdmDTRLoss
mdmDTRLoss.description: Mask for loss of DTR alarm.

mdmRxdTran.name: mdmRxdTran
mdmRxdTran.description: Mask for Receive data transitions alarm.

mdmTxdTran.name: mdmTxdTran
mdmTxdTran.description: Mask for transmit data transitions alarm.

mdmDCDLoss.name: mdmDCDLoss
mdmDCDLoss.description: Mask for loss of DCD alarm.

mdmRingNoAnswer.name: mdmRingNoAnswer
mdmRingNoAnswer.description: Mask for Rings no Answer alarm.

mdmRetrain.name: mdmRetrain
mdmRetrain.description: Mask for Retrains count exceeded alarm.

mdmCallLength.name: mdmCallLength
mdmCallLength.description: Mask for Call Length exceeded alarm.

mdmConfigErr.name: mdmConfigErr
mdmConfigErr.description: Mask for Configuration checksum error alarm.

mdmSignalQuality.name: mdmSignalQuality
mdmSignalQuality.description: Mask for Poor Signal Quality alarm.

mdmOnDBU.name: mdmOnDBU
mdmOnDBU.description: Mask for On Dial Backup alarm.

mdmThresholdsTable.name: mdmThresholdsTable
mdmThresholdsTable.description: The GDC VFAST Alarm Thresholds Table.

mdmThresholdsEntry.name: mdmThresholdsEntry
mdmThresholdsEntry.description: An entry in the GDC VFAST Alarm Thresholds table.

mdmThresholdsIndex.name: mdmThresholdsIndex
mdmThresholdsIndex.description: This object is the identifier of the Thresholds table.

mdmCallDuration.name: mdmCallDuration
mdmCallDuration.description: This option selects the call duration threshold for alarm.

mdmRetrainThreshold.name: mdmRetrainThreshold
mdmRetrainThreshold.description: This option selects the number of retrains threshold for alarm.

mdmStatusEntry.name: mdmStatusEntry
mdmStatusEntry.description: An entry in the GDC VFAST Status table.

mdmStatusIndex.name: mdmStatusIndex
mdmStatusIndex.description: This object is the identifier of the VFAST Status table.

mdmPLLookbackStatus.name: mdmPLLookbackStatus
mdmPLLookbackStatus.description: Shows the status of Private Line lookback.

mdmAutoDialRestoralStatus.name: mdmAutoDialRestoralStatus
mdmAutoDialRestoralStatus.description: Shows the status of Auto Dial Restoral.

mdmTXDtransitions.name: mdmTXDtransitions
mdmTXDtransitions.description: EIA Status of TXD data transitions.

mdmRXDtransitions.name: mdmRXDtransitions
mdmRXDtransitions.description: EIA Status of RXD data transitions.

mdmRTStransitions.name: mdmRTStransitions
mdmRTStransitions.description: EIA Status of Request to Send transitions.

mdmDTRtransitions.name: mdmDTRtransitions
mdmDTRtransitions.description: EIA Status of Data Terminal Ready transitions.

mdmDCDtransitions.name: mdmDCDtransitions
mdmDCDtransitions.description: EIA Status of Carrier Detect transitions.

mdmDTR.name: mdmDTR
mdmDTR.description: EIA Status of Data Terminal Ready.

mdmCTS.name: mdmCTS
mdmCTS.description: EIA Status of Clear to Send.

mdmDSR.name: mdmDSR
mdmDSR.description: EIA Status of Data Set Ready.

mdmRTS.name: mdmRTS
mdmRTS.description: EIA Status of Request to Send.

mdmSwitchedPrivate.name: mdmSwitchedPrivate
mdmSwitchedPrivate.description: Switched Network or Private Line configuration setting.

mdmControlEntry.name: mdmControlEntry
mdmControlEntry.description: An entry in the GDC VFAST Control table.

mdmControlIndex.name: mdmControlIndex
mdmControlIndex.description: This object is the identifier of the VFAST Control table.

mdmSoftReset.name: mdmSoftReset
mdmSoftReset.description: Forces a soft reset on the modem. Not applicable when the modem is in Remote Configuration session.

mdmFrontPanel.name: mdmFrontPanel
mdmFrontPanel.description: This command controls the functionality of the front panel Switches.

mdmMakeClearBusy.name: mdmMakeClearBusy
mdmMakeClearBusy.description: Command used to control the Offhook relay to make busy or clear the VF line. Not applicable when the modem is in Remote Configuration session.

mdmPLTalkData.name: mdmPLTalkData
mdmPLTalkData.description: Object is used to force the modem to the idle or data state while configured for Private line. Idle, allows the modem to activate the private line option. Data, forces the modem to retrain.

mdmWhatAreYouTable.name: mdmWhatAreYouTable
mdmWhatAreYouTable.description: The GDC VFAST What Are You Table.

mdmWhatAreYouEntry.name: mdmWhatAreYouEntry
mdmWhatAreYouEntry.description: An entry in the GDC VFAST What Are You table.

mdmWhatAreYouIndex.name: mdmWhatAreYouIndex
mdmWhatAreYouIndex.description: This object is the identifier of the VFAST What Are You table.

mdmVFCard.name: mdmVFCard
mdmVFCard.description: This function returns the value the VF card attached to the modem.

mdmDTECard.name: mdmDTECard
mdmDTECard.description: This function returns the type of DTE card attached to the modem.

mdmProductCode.name: mdmProductCode
mdmProductCode.description: This identifies what type of device this is.

mdmCodeRev.name: mdmCodeRev
mdmCodeRev.description: This function returns the firmware code level. example 01 - A- 02 - B-

mdmBootRev.name: mdmBootRev
mdmBootRev.description: This function returns the boot firmware level. example 01 - A- 02 - B-

mdmCountryCode.name: mdmCountryCode
mdmCountryCode.description: This function returns the country code number in three bytes. Each byte is the hex value of an decimal number. Example hex 30,30,31 is the country code of USA 001 30,34,34 is the country code of UK 044

mdmDiagnosticTable.name: mdmDiagnosticTable
mdmDiagnosticTable.description: The GDC VFAST diagnostics table. Not applicable when the modem is in Remote Configuration session.

mdmDiagnosticEntry.name: mdmDiagnosticEntry
mdmDiagnosticEntry.description: A listing of GDC VFAST diagnostic tests

mdmDiagnosticIndex.name: mdmDiagnosticIndex
mdmDiagnosticIndex.description: A unique index for the Diagnostic Table.

mdmDiagnosticTest.name: mdmDiagnosticTest
mdmDiagnosticTest.description: This function selects the test. Not applicable when the modem is in Remote Configuration session.

mdmDiagnosticResults.name: mdmDiagnosticResults
mdmDiagnosticResults.description: This function reads the test results in bit errors.

mdmDiagnosticStatus.name: mdmDiagnosticStatus
mdmDiagnosticStatus.description: Diagnostic status of which test is running. Not applicable when the modem is in Remote Configuration session.

mdmTestStatus.name: mdmTestStatus
mdmTestStatus.description: Test Status canNotBeDone - means test can not be done at this time terminated - means the test was terminated, could be terminated via the front panel timedout - the modem's test timer expired noPrevStatus - means that no status is currently available Not applicable when the modem is in Remote Configuration session.

mdmTestDuration.name: mdmTestDuration
mdmTestDuration.description: Time of modem in test, counted in timeticks. Not applicable when the modem is in Remote Configuration session.

mdmDialingFunctionTable.name: mdmDialingFunctionTable
mdmDialingFunctionTable.description: The GDC VFAST modem dialing function table.

mdmDialingFunctionEntry.name: mdmDialingFunctionEntry
mdmDialingFunctionEntry.description: A listing of GDC VFAST modem dialing function parameters.

mdmDialFunctionIndex.name: mdmDialFunctionIndex
mdmDialFunctionIndex.description: A unique index for the Dialing Function Table.

mdmManualDial.name: mdmManualDial
mdmManualDial.description: Command to instruct the modem to dial the following number, n. Not applicable when modem in remote configuration session.

mdmTerminateCall.name: mdmTerminateCall
mdmTerminateCall.description: Command to instruct the mode to disconnect the call and go to idle.

mdmDialStatus.name: mdmDialStatus

mdmMIBVersion.name: mdmMIBVersion

When a release is complete no T should exist.
